%S A395247 1,1,0,1,2,0,1,15,9,0,1,124,318,100,0,1,1295,12660,12610,2715,0,1,
%T A395247 16806,679095,1860440,1049475,175686,0,1,262143,50479653,384313755,
%U A395247 487070115,190183077,26470521,0
%N A395247 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of acyclic digraphs (or DAGs) on n labeled nodes in which the maximum in-degree is k, for n >= 0 and 0 <= k <= n.
%C A395247 Row sums give A003024 (all labeled DAGs).
%C A395247 T(n,0) = 1 (the empty digraph).
%C A395247 T(n,n) = 0 for n >= 1, since a DAG on n nodes has maximum in-degree at most n-1.
%C A395247 T(n,1) = (n+1)^(n-1) - 1 = A000272(n+1) - 1: DAGs with maximum in-degree exactly 1 are the nonempty labeled forests of rooted trees.
%C A395247 Partial row sums Sum_{j=0..k} T(n,j) count DAGs with in-degree at most k.
%H A395247 Tyler Satchel Orden, <a href="/A395247/b395247.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..189</a>
%F A395247 T(n,k) = A(n,k) - A(n,k-1) for k >= 1, where A(n,k) is the number of labeled DAGs on n nodes with every in-degree at most k, computable by the level-decomposition sum in A397711 with F(p,q) = Sum_{i=1..k} (binomial(p+q,i) - binomial(q,i)).
%e A395247 Triangle begins:
%e A395247   1;
%e A395247   1, 0;
%e A395247   1, 2, 0;
%e A395247   1, 15, 9, 0;
%e A395247   1, 124, 318, 100, 0;
%e A395247   1, 1295, 12660, 12610, 2715, 0;
%e A395247 For n = 3: of the 25 DAGs on 3 labeled nodes, 1 is empty, 15 have maximum in-degree 1, 9 have a node of in-degree 2, and none have in-degree 3, so row 3 is 1, 15, 9, 0.
%o A395247 (Python) # T(n,k) = a(n,k) - a(n,k-1) with a(n,k) as in A397711.
%Y A395247 Cf. A003024 (row sums), A000272 (column k=1, shifted), A397711 (partial row sums, k=2), A397712 (partial row sums, k=3).
%K A395247 nonn,tabl,new
%O A395247 0,5
